title: Suitable Flesh
review: This is camp and fun. There's a clever monster that you never really see, who's real form could be timeless and incomprehensible to us mortals. The psychiatrist surely doesn't comply with her industry's standards and practices here. This movie does that thing where someone's personality has switched to evil mode, and their eyebrows are going wild, and they're winking straight at the camera, but nobody else notices.
